      'open-source.s2.l7': 'Cryptography and secure storage helpers',
      'open-source.s2.l8': 'Testing, linting, and build tooling (development only)',
      'open-source.s2.p': 'The Pinfold App is developed using Flutter and Dart. It includes OSS packages from the pub.dev ecosystem and the\n  Flutter SDK, which are subject to the BSD-style licenses and other terms published by the Flutter authors and\n  individual package maintainers.',
      'open-source.s2.p2': 'Representative categories of OSS used in the mobile App include:',
      'open-source.s2.title': '2. Mobile application (Flutter / Dart)',
      'open-source.s3.l1': 'ASP.NET Core web framework and middleware',
      'open-source.s3.l2': 'Entity Framework Core and database providers',
      'open-source.s3.l3': 'JSON serialization, logging, and dependency injection libraries',
      'open-source.s3.l4': 'HTTP clients and cloud SDK helpers',
      'open-source.s3.l5': 'Security, JWT, and cryptography packages',
      'open-source.s3.l6': 'Testing and code analysis tools (development only)',
      'open-source.s3.p': 'Pinfold backend services are built on Microsoft .NET and incorporate OSS NuGet packages under licenses such as MIT,\n  Apache License 2.0, and BSD.',
      'open-source.s3.p2': 'Representative categories of OSS used in backend services include:',
      'open-source.s3.title': '3. Backend services (.NET)',
      'open-source.s4.l1': '<strong>MIT License',
      'open-source.s4.l2': '<strong>Apache License 2.0',
      'open-source.s4.l3': '<strong>BSD Licenses (2-Clause / 3-Clause)',
      'open-source.s4.l4': '<strong>Mozilla Public License 2.0',
      'open-source.s4.l5': '<strong>LGPL / GPL family',
      'open-source.s4.p': 'OSS components in the Service may be licensed under one or more of the following (among others):',
      'open-source.s4.p2': 'Each component is governed by its own license. Nothing in this notice modifies or overrides the terms of any\n  applicable OSS license.',
      'open-source.s4.title': '4. Common license types',
      'open-source.s5.p': 'OSS components are distinct from Pinfold&rsquo;s proprietary application code, branding, and original content.\n  Proprietary portions remain subject to our EULA and Terms of Service. Inclusion of OSS does not make the entire\n  Service open source or grant you rights to Pinfold&rsquo;s proprietary intellectual property.',
      'open-source.s5.title': '5. Pinfold proprietary code',
      'open-source.s6.l1': 'Mobile App: available in the App&rsquo;s Settings â†’ About â†’ Open Source Licenses (or equivalent) screen, where provided.',
      'open-source.s6.l2': 'Backend: maintained in source repository NOTICE files and package dependency manifests.',
      'open-source.s6.l3': 'Upon request: we will provide additional attribution information to the extent reasonably practicable.',
      'open-source.s6.p': 'Copyright notices, license texts, and required attributions for OSS components are maintained as follows:',
      'open-source.s6.title': '6. License texts and attributions',
      'open-source.s7.p': 'If the Service includes OSS governed by a license that requires offer of corresponding source code, you may request\n  such source by contacting\n  <a href="mailto:support@pinfoldai.com?subject=Open%20source%20source%20code%20request">support@pinfoldai.com',
      'open-source.s7.title': '7. Source code offers (copyleft components)',
      'open-source.s8.p': 'OSS components are provided by their respective authors &ldquo;AS IS&rdquo; without warranty of any kind. Pinfold\n  disclaims all warranties with respect to OSS to the maximum extent permitted by law, except as stated in individual\n  OSS licenses.',
      'open-source.s8.title': '8. No warranty for OSS',
      'open-source.s9.p': 'OSS dependencies change between App and server releases as we update packages for security, compatibility, and\n  features. The list of components and versions is therefore not static. This notice will be updated periodically;\n  see the &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date above.',
      'open-source.s9.title': '9. Updates',
      'open-source.seealso': 'See also:\n  <a href="/legal/license.html">License &amp; Disclaimer',
      'open-source.title': 'Open Source Software Notice',
      'privacy.intro': 'Pinfold AI (&ldquo;Pinfold,&rdquo; &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us&rdquo;) operates the Pinfold mobile application (<code>com.pinfoldai.fileexplorer',
      'privacy.meta': 'Last updated: July 6, 2026 · Version 2026-07-06',
      'privacy.s1.p': 'Pinfold AI is the data controller for personal data processed through the Service, except where we act as a processor on behalf of a business customer under a separate agreement. For privacy inquiries, contact our Data Protection Officer at <a href="mailto:support@pinfoldai.com?subject=Privacy%20inquiry">support@pinfoldai.com',
      'privacy.s1.title': '1. Data controller and contact',
      'privacy.s10.l1': 'Account data is retained while your Account is active and for a reasonable period afterward for backup, dispute resolution, and legal compliance',
      'privacy.s10.l2': 'Temporary social upload copies are deleted after publishing completes or within 30 days, whichever is sooner',
      'privacy.s10.l3': 'OAuth tokens are deleted when you disconnect an integration or delete your Account',
      'privacy.s10.l4': 'Billing and transaction records may be retained as required for tax, accounting, and fraud prevention (typically up to 7 years where required)',
      'privacy.s10.l5': 'Support tickets and abuse reports may be retained to handle follow-up and enforce policies',
      'privacy.s10.l6': 'Logs and analytics data are retained for limited periods based on operational need, then deleted or aggregated',
      'privacy.s10.title': '10. Data retention',
      'privacy.s11.p': 'We implement technical and organizational measures including HTTPS encryption in transit, encrypted token storage on servers, access controls, and industry-standard security practices. No method of transmission or storage is 100% secure. You are responsible for your device passcode, app lock PIN, vault passphrase, and security of connected Third-Party Service accounts. Report suspected security issues to support@pinfoldai.com promptly.',
      'privacy.s11.title': '11. Security measures',
      'privacy.s12.p': 'Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, restrict, or object to processing of your personal data, to data portability, and to withdraw consent where processing is consent-based. The table below summarizes common rights. Some rights are subject to exceptions under applicable law.',
      'privacy.s12.p2': 'We will respond to verified requests within the timeframe required by applicable law (typically 30 days under GDPR, 45 days under CCPA/CPRA). We may need to verify your identity before fulfilling requests.',
      'privacy.s12.table.h1': 'Right',
      'privacy.s12.table.h2': 'Description',
      'privacy.s12.table.h3': 'How to exercise',
      'privacy.s12.table.r1c1': 'Access',
      'privacy.s12.table.r1c2': 'Obtain a copy of personal data we hold about you',
      'privacy.s12.table.r1c3': 'Email DPO or use in-app account export where available',
      'privacy.s12.table.r2c1': 'Correction',
